rComments: Memorize everything. EVERYTHING. She's very clear and precise in class and her notes are very easy to follow understand. Only thing is that all of her questions I found to be very specific. Know it all! All those enzymes, all the pathways and their intersections ... even the stats!

the material is fairly dry so she does her best at including examples and relating metabolism to our daily lives. her exams are fair but you need to study a lot for a decent grade.. its a lot of memorization (enzymes, pathways etc)

I really enjoyed her Metabolism class. Albeit a difficult subject to teach since it requires that students familiarize themselves with many metabolic pathways, Dr. Harper did a great job at making the subject matter relevant.
relatively boring, reads off slides, test material inconsistent with notes and suggesting studying - makes it very difficult to view midterms/exams
Prof makes it really difficult to view midterms.  Lectures consist of her just reading slides...
